        "text": "From holiday markets to the beautiful Plitvice Lakes, the country is the best destination for a winter getaway. So, if you’re looking to book a trip soon, we’ve gathered the best seven reasons you need to go to Croatia:\n\n3. Croatia Offers Stunning, Empty Beaches\n\nCroatia is a beautiful country with a lot to offer tourists, and one of the best things about it is that there are plenty of beaches to enjoy, even in winter.\n\nWhile the Mediterranean Sea is too cold for swimming in winter, the Adriatic Sea remains relatively warm. This means that you can still enjoy the beach in Croatia, even when it’s not bikini weather.\n\nMoreover, there are plenty of beaches in Croatia that are less crowded in winter. This is because most tourists flock to the country in summer when the weather is better. If you’re looking for a quiet beach, this is the place!\n\nThe best time to visit Croatia’s beaches is from April to October. However, if you don’t mind the cooler temperatures, you’ll find that the beaches are less crowded in winter. This is the perfect time to enjoy the peace and quiet of the Croatian coastline, so why not make your Christmas more special?\n\n4. Croatia Is Home to the Beautiful Plitvice Lakes\n\nCroatia is home to the beautiful Plitvice Lakes, which are a series of 16 interconnected lakes that are fed by a number of rivers and waterfalls. The lakes are renowned for their crystal-clear water and stunning scenery and are popular tourist destinations.\n\nThe Plitvice Lakes are located in the Plitvice National Park, situated in the central part of Croatia. The park covers an area of 300 square kilometers and is home to a number of different plant and animal species.\n\nThe Plitvice Lakes are a popular destination for hikers, as there are a number of trails that lead through the park. The lakes are also a popular destination for photographers, as the scenery is truly breathtaking.\n\nIf you plan a trip to Croatia, then book a guided tour to Plitvice Lakes. You won’t be disappointed!\n\nTake a look at our best-value Plitvice Lakes Tours!\n\nKey Things to Know Before You Book a Winter Trip to Croatia\n\nThis Mediterranean country has a lot to offer, but you should know a few visiting tips before you book your trip, so read on for our top tips.\n\n1. The Weather\n\nCroatia is a Mediterranean country, meaning you can expect mild winters with occasional rain. The average temperature in December is around 10 degrees Celsius, so pack your sweaters!\n\n2. The Cost\n\nCroatia is a relatively affordable destination, especially compared to other European countries. You can expect to pay around $50 per day for a mid-range hotel room and $30 for a meal in a restaurant.\n\n3. The Language\n\nThe official language in Croatia is Croatian, but you’ll find that many people speak English, especially in tourist areas. It pays to know a phrase or two, though!\n\n4. The Visa Situation\n\nIf you’re a citizen of the United States, Canada, or Australia, you do not need a visa to enter Croatia. However, you will need a valid passport.\n\n5. The Safety\n\nCroatia is a relatively safe country to travel to, but you should always take precautions when traveling in any foreign country. Be sure to research the local laws and customs before you go, and always carry your passport with you."
